#     PI_NAME                         Herbert Funsten
#     PI_AFFILIATION                  Los Alamos National Laboratory
#     TEXT                            Pitch angle binned data from the HOPE plasma spectrometer.  Note that there                            
#     TEXT                             are no correections performed on the data (e.g. background subtraction, velocity                      
#                                      corrections, etc.)

#     LOGICAL_SOURCE_DESCRIPTION      Pitch angle resolved ECT-HOPE science data.  Electron fluxes ~15-50,000 eV,                            
#                                      ion fluxes ~1-50,000 eV. Electrons and ions measured in alternate spin cadence.

#       NOTES:  TImebase for ion measurements
#  2. Half sample time
#       NOTES:  Half the HOPE frame time
#  3. FPDO: Omnidirectional differential Proton flux ~1-50,000 eV
#       NOTES:  Proton flux integrated (piecewise constant) over pitch angle (11) and gyro angle (20) as computed from magnetic field direction crossed with spacecraft spin axis and energy (72).  Note that data have been expanded to the highest possible resolution, even though before 9/2013 the transmitted data are collapsed (36 energies, 4-8-16-8-4 spin angles) to fit the telemetry allocation.
#  4. ---> HOPE_ENERGY_Ion
#       NOTES:  Energy for Ion measuremnts. Note that HOPE normally measures 72 energy steps; before 9/2013 adjacent channels were combined for downlink.  Those are then expanded on the ground into 72 channels again.
#
#  
# Key Parameter and Survey data (labels K0,K1,K2) are preliminary browse data.

#       NOTES:  Oxygen flux integrated (piecewise constant) over pitch angle (11) and gyro angle (20) as computed from magnetic field direction crossed with spacecraft spin axis and energy (72). VariableDescription.Header:
#              ************************************
#              *****    GLOBAL ATTRIBUTES    ******
#              ************************************
#
#     PROJECT                         LWS>Living With a Star
#     SOURCE_NAME                     RBSP-B>Radiation Belt Storm Probe B
#     DISCIPLINE                      Space Physics>Magnetospheric Science
#     DATA_TYPE                       rel02>Release 02
#     DESCRIPTOR                      ECT-HOPE-PA-L3>ECT Helium Oxygen Proton Electron Plasma Analyszer Fluxes by                            
#                                      Pitch Angle Level 3                                                                                   
#     DATA_VERSION                    01
#     PI_NAME                         Herbert Funsten
#     PI_AFFILIATION                  Los Alamos National Laboratory
#     TEXT                            Pitch angle binned data from the HOPE plasma spectrometer.  Note that there                            
#     TEXT                             are no correections performed on the data (e.g. background subtraction, velocity                      
#                                      corrections, etc.)                                                                                    
#     INSTRUMENT_TYPE                 Particles (space)
#     MISSION_GROUP                   Van Allen Probes (RBSP)
#     LOGICAL_SOURCE                  rbspb_rel02_ect-hope-pa-l3
#     LOGICAL_FILE_ID                 rbsp-b_l3_ect-hope_00000000_v01
#     LOGICAL_SOURCE_DESCRIPTION      Pitch angle resolved ECT-HOPE science data.  Electron fluxes ~15-50,000 eV,                            
#                                      ion fluxes ~1-50,000 eV. Electrons and ions measured in alternate spin cadence.                       
#     GENERATED_BY                    LANL
#     GENERATION_DATE                 20140827
#     ACKNOWLEDGEMENT                 Herb Funsten, Ruth Skoug, Reiner Friedel
#     MODS                            CDF skeleton version of 20120705. Written by R. Friedel.
#                                     20120706 version written by R. Skoug.
#                                     20130715 revisions by J. T. Niehof.
#                                     20130808 revisions by J. T. Niehof/BA Larsen.
#                                     20130927 revision (remove per-mode variables)by J. T. Niehof.
#     ADID_REF                        NSSD0110
#     LINK_TEXT                       ECT home page
#                                     ECT SOC and data services
#                                     Van Allen Probes
#     LINK_TITLE                      at UNH
#                                     at LANL
#                                     Science Gateway (including Mission Rules of the Road for Data Usage)
#     HTTP_LINK                       http://rbsp-ect.sr.unh.edu
#                                     http://www.rbsp-ect.lanl.gov
#                                     http://rbspgway.jhuapl.edu/
#     FILE_NAMING_CONVENTION          source_descriptor_datatype
#     RULES_OF_USE                    Distribute freely, acknowledge original PI. Please contact PI before any publication                   
#                                      or presentation of data.                                                                              
#     CDAWLIB_IDL_ROW_NOTRANSPOSE     TRUE
#
#              ************************************
#              ****  RECORD VARYING VARIABLES  ****
#              ************************************
#
#  1. Timebase for ion measurments
#       NOTES:  TImebase for ion measurements
#  2. Half sample time
#       NOTES:  Half the HOPE frame time
#  3. ---> HOPE proton counts OMNI
#       NOTES:  Proton counts summed over pitch angle (11) and gyro angle (20) as computed from magnetic field direction crossed with spacecraft spin axis and energy (72).  Note that data have been expanded to the highest possible resolution, even though before 9/2013 the transmitted data are collapsed (36 energies, 4-8-16-8-4 spin angles) to fit the telemetry allocation. Counts are summed over all measurements in a PA/gyro bin.
#  4. ---> HOPE_ENERGY_Ion
#       NOTES:  Energy for Ion measuremnts. Note that HOPE normally measures 72 energy steps; before 9/2013 adjacent channels were combined for downlink.  Those are then expanded on the ground into 72 channels again.
#
#  
# Key Parameter and Survey data (labels K0,K1,K2) are preliminary browse data.
# Generated by CDAWeb on: Thu Jan 15 22:35:05 2015

#              ************************************
#              *****    GLOBAL ATTRIBUTES    ******
#              ************************************
#
#     PROJECT                         LWS>Living With a Star
#     SOURCE_NAME                     RBSP-B>Radiation Belt Storm Probe B
#     DISCIPLINE                      Space Physics>Magnetospheric Science
#     DATA_TYPE                       rel02>Release 02
#     DESCRIPTOR                      ECT-HOPE-PA-L3>ECT Helium Oxygen Proton Electron Plasma Analyszer Fluxes by                            
#                                      Pitch Angle Level 3                                                                                   
#     DATA_VERSION                    01
#     PI_NAME                         Herbert Funsten
#     PI_AFFILIATION                  Los Alamos National Laboratory
#     TEXT                            Pitch angle binned data from the HOPE plasma spectrometer.  Note that there                            
#     TEXT                             are no correections performed on the data (e.g. background subtraction, velocity                      
#                                      corrections, etc.)                                                                                    
#     INSTRUMENT_TYPE                 Particles (space)
#     MISSION_GROUP                   Van Allen Probes (RBSP)
#     LOGICAL_SOURCE                  rbspb_rel02_ect-hope-pa-l3
#     LOGICAL_FILE_ID                 rbsp-b_l3_ect-hope_00000000_v01
#     LOGICAL_SOURCE_DESCRIPTION      Pitch angle resolved ECT-HOPE science data.  Electron fluxes ~15-50,000 eV,                            
#                                      ion fluxes ~1-50,000 eV. Electrons and ions measured in alternate spin cadence.                       
#     GENERATED_BY                    LANL
#     GENERATION_DATE                 20140827
#     ACKNOWLEDGEMENT                 Herb Funsten, Ruth Skoug, Reiner Friedel
#     MODS                            CDF skeleton version of 20120705. Written by R. Friedel.
#                                     20120706 version written by R. Skoug.
#                                     20130715 revisions by J. T. Niehof.
#                                     20130808 revisions by J. T. Niehof/BA Larsen.
#                                     20130927 revision (remove per-mode variables)by J. T. Niehof.
#     ADID_REF                        NSSD0110
#     LINK_TEXT                       ECT home page
#                                     ECT SOC and data services
#                                     Van Allen Probes
#     LINK_TITLE                      at UNH
#                                     at LANL
#                                     Science Gateway (including Mission Rules of the Road for Data Usage)
#     HTTP_LINK                       http://rbsp-ect.sr.unh.edu
#                                     http://www.rbsp-ect.lanl.gov
#                                     http://rbspgway.jhuapl.edu/
#     FILE_NAMING_CONVENTION          source_descriptor_datatype
#     RULES_OF_USE                    Distribute freely, acknowledge original PI. Please contact PI before any publication                   
#                                      or presentation of data.                                                                              
#     CDAWLIB_IDL_ROW_NOTRANSPOSE     TRUE
#
#              ************************************
#              ****  RECORD VARYING VARIABLES  ****
#              ************************************
#
#  1. Timebase for ion measurments
#       NOTES:  TImebase for ion measurements
#  2. Half sample time
#       NOTES:  Half the HOPE frame time
#  3. ---> HOPE helium counts OMNI
#       NOTES:  Helium counts summed over pitch angle (11) and gyro angle (20) as computed from magnetic field direction crossed with spacecraft spin axis and energy (72).  Note that data have been expanded to the highest possible resolution, even though before 9/2013 the transmitted data are collapsed (36 energies, 4-8-16-8-4 spin angles) to fit the telemetry allocation. Counts are summed over all measurements in a PA/gyro bin.
#  4. ---> HOPE_ENERGY_Ion
#       NOTES:  Energy for Ion measuremnts. Note that HOPE normally measures 72 energy steps; before 9/2013 adjacent channels were combined for downlink.  Those are then expanded on the ground into 72 channels again.
#

VariableDescription.Header:
#              ************************************
#              *****    GLOBAL ATTRIBUTES    ******
#              ************************************
#
#     PROJECT                         LWS>Living With a Star
#     SOURCE_NAME                     RBSP-B>Radiation Belt Storm Probe B
#     DISCIPLINE                      Space Physics>Magnetospheric Science
#     DATA_TYPE                       rel02>Release 02
#     DESCRIPTOR                      ECT-HOPE-PA-L3>ECT Helium Oxygen Proton Electron Plasma Analyszer Fluxes by                            
#                                      Pitch Angle Level 3                                                                                   
#     DATA_VERSION                    01
#     PI_NAME                         Herbert Funsten
#     PI_AFFILIATION                  Los Alamos National Laboratory
#     TEXT                            Pitch angle binned data from the HOPE plasma spectrometer.  Note that there                            
#     TEXT                             are no correections performed on the data (e.g. background subtraction, velocity                      
#                                      corrections, etc.)                                                                                    
#     INSTRUMENT_TYPE                 Particles (space)
#     MISSION_GROUP                   Van Allen Probes (RBSP)
#     LOGICAL_SOURCE                  rbspb_rel02_ect-hope-pa-l3
#     LOGICAL_FILE_ID                 rbsp-b_l3_ect-hope_00000000_v01
#     LOGICAL_SOURCE_DESCRIPTION      Pitch angle resolved ECT-HOPE science data.  Electron fluxes ~15-50,000 eV,                            
#                                      ion fluxes ~1-50,000 eV. Electrons and ions measured in alternate spin cadence.                       
#     GENERATED_BY                    LANL
#     GENERATION_DATE                 20140827
#     ACKNOWLEDGEMENT                 Herb Funsten, Ruth Skoug, Reiner Friedel
#     MODS                            CDF skeleton version of 20120705. Written by R. Friedel.
#                                     20120706 version written by R. Skoug.
#                                     20130715 revisions by J. T. Niehof.
#                                     20130808 revisions by J. T. Niehof/BA Larsen.
#                                     20130927 revision (remove per-mode variables)by J. T. Niehof.
#     ADID_REF                        NSSD0110
#     LINK_TEXT                       ECT home page
#                                     ECT SOC and data services
#                                     Van Allen Probes
#     LINK_TITLE                      at UNH
#                                     at LANL
#                                     Science Gateway (including Mission Rules of the Road for Data Usage)
#     HTTP_LINK                       http://rbsp-ect.sr.unh.edu
#                                     http://www.rbsp-ect.lanl.gov
#                                     http://rbspgway.jhuapl.edu/
#     FILE_NAMING_CONVENTION          source_descriptor_datatype
#     RULES_OF_USE                    Distribute freely, acknowledge original PI. Please contact PI before any publication                   
#                                      or presentation of data.                                                                              
#     CDAWLIB_IDL_ROW_NOTRANSPOSE     TRUE
#
#              ************************************
#              ****  RECORD VARYING VARIABLES  ****
#              ************************************
#
#  1. Timebase for ion measurments
#       NOTES:  TImebase for ion measurements
#  2. Half sample time
#       NOTES:  Half the HOPE frame time
#  3. ---> HOPE Oxygen counts OMNI
#       NOTES:  Oxygen counts summed over pitch angle (11) and gyro angle (20) as computed from magnetic field direction crossed with spacecraft spin axis and energy (72).  Note that data have been expanded to the highest possible resolution, even though before 9/2013 the transmitted data are collapsed (36 energies, 4-8-16-8-4 spin angles) to fit the telemetry allocation. Counts are summed over all measurements in a PA/gyro bin.
#  4. ---> HOPE_ENERGY_Ion
#       NOTES:  Energy for Ion measuremnts. Note that HOPE normally measures 72 energy steps; before 9/2013 adjacent channels were combined for downlink.  Those are then expanded on the ground into 72 channels again.
#
#

#              ************************************
#              *****    GLOBAL ATTRIBUTES    ******
#              ************************************
#
#     PROJECT                         LWS>Living With a Star
#     SOURCE_NAME                     RBSP-B>Radiation Belt Storm Probe B
#     DISCIPLINE                      Space Physics>Magnetospheric Science
#     DATA_TYPE                       rel02>Release 02
#     DESCRIPTOR                      ECT-HOPE-PA-L3>ECT Helium Oxygen Proton Electron Plasma Analyszer Fluxes by                            
#                                      Pitch Angle Level 3                                                                                   
#     DATA_VERSION                    01
#     PI_NAME                         Herbert Funsten
#     PI_AFFILIATION                  Los Alamos National Laboratory
#     TEXT                            Pitch angle binned data from the HOPE plasma spectrometer.  Note that there                            
#     TEXT                             are no correections performed on the data (e.g. background subtraction, velocity                      
#                                      corrections, etc.)                                                                                    
#     INSTRUMENT_TYPE                 Particles (space)
#     MISSION_GROUP                   Van Allen Probes (RBSP)
#     LOGICAL_SOURCE                  rbspb_rel02_ect-hope-pa-l3
#     LOGICAL_FILE_ID                 rbsp-b_l3_ect-hope_00000000_v01
#     LOGICAL_SOURCE_DESCRIPTION      Pitch angle resolved ECT-HOPE science data.  Electron fluxes ~15-50,000 eV,                            
#                                      ion fluxes ~1-50,000 eV. Electrons and ions measured in alternate spin cadence.                       
#     GENERATED_BY                    LANL
#     GENERATION_DATE                 20140827
#     ACKNOWLEDGEMENT                 Herb Funsten, Ruth Skoug, Reiner Friedel
#     MODS                            CDF skeleton version of 20120705. Written by R. Friedel.
#                                     20120706 version written by R. Skoug.
#                                     20130715 revisions by J. T. Niehof.
#                                     20130808 revisions by J. T. Niehof/BA Larsen.
#                                     20130927 revision (remove per-mode variables)by J. T. Niehof.
#     ADID_REF                        NSSD0110
#     LINK_TEXT                       ECT home page
#                                     ECT SOC and data services
#                                     Van Allen Probes
#     LINK_TITLE                      at UNH
#                                     at LANL
#                                     Science Gateway (including Mission Rules of the Road for Data Usage)
#     HTTP_LINK                       http://rbsp-ect.sr.unh.edu
#                                     http://www.rbsp-ect.lanl.gov
#                                     http://rbspgway.jhuapl.edu/
#     FILE_NAMING_CONVENTION          source_descriptor_datatype
#     RULES_OF_USE                    Distribute freely, acknowledge original PI. Please contact PI before any publication                   
#                                      or presentation of data.                                                                              
#     CDAWLIB_IDL_ROW_NOTRANSPOSE     TRUE
#
#              ************************************
#              ****  RECORD VARYING VARIABLES  ****
#              ************************************
#
#  1. Timebase for electron measurments
#       NOTES:  TImebase for electron heasurements
#  2. Half sample time
#       NOTES:  Half the HOPE frame time
#  3. ---> No. samples for FEDO
#       NOTES:  Number of samples used in computing the flux summed over pitch angle. #              ************************************

#     PROJECT                         LWS>Living With a Star

#                                      Pitch Angle Level 3

#     PI_NAME                         Herbert Funsten
#     PI_AFFILIATION                  Los Alamos National Laboratory
#     TEXT                            Pitch angle binned data from the HOPE plasma spectrometer.  Note that there                            
#     TEXT                             are no correections performed on the data (e.g. background subtraction, velocity                      
#                                      corrections, etc.)                                                                                    
#     INSTRUMENT_TYPE                 Particles (space)
#     MISSION_GROUP                   Van Allen Probes (RBSP)
#     LOGICAL_SOURCE                  rbspb_rel02_ect-hope-pa-l3
#     LOGICAL_FILE_ID                 rbsp-b_l3_ect-hope_00000000_v01
#     LOGICAL_SOURCE_DESCRIPTION      Pitch angle resolved ECT-HOPE science data.  Electron fluxes ~15-50,000 eV,                            
#                                      ion fluxes ~1-50,000 eV. Electrons and ions measured in alternate spin cadence.                       
#     GENERATED_BY                    LANL

#              ************************************
#
#  1. Timebase for ion measurments
#       NOTES:  TImebase for ion measurements
#  2. Half sample time
#       NOTES:  Half the HOPE frame time
#  3. ---> No. samples FIDO
#       NOTES:  Number of samples used in computing the flux summed over pitch angle.  Note that data have been expanded to the highest possible resolution (16 spin angles, 72 energies), even though before 9/2013 the transmitted data are collapsed (36 energies, 4-8-16-8-4 spin angles) to fit the telemetry allocation.
#  4. ---> HOPE_ENERGY_Ion
#       NOTES:  Energy for Ion measuremnts. Note that HOPE normally measures 72 energy steps; before 9/2013 adjacent channels were combined for downlink.  Those are then expanded on the ground into 72 channels again.
